er": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Walk the town and the Tâmega riverside, climb or drive Monte Farinha to the Santuário de Nossa Senhora da Graça for the panoramic view, visit the Fisgas de Ermelo waterfalls in the Alvão natural park, and — if your timing is lucky — join the town's Viniculum wine festival in the squares."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Do you need a car in Mondim de Basto?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "The town itself is walkable, but you'll want a car, taxi or guided tour to reach Monte Farinha's summit sanctuary and the Fisgas de Ermelo waterfalls. There is no public transport up the mountain."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "When is the best time to visit Mondim de Basto?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Late spring through summer for the warm evenings, the green countryside and the town's festivals — including the sanctuary pilgrimages (late May, 25 July, early September) and the local wine festival. Outside summer the town is peaceful but very quiet."}}]}]};
